Hello everyone.
I have a problem with the “hs_execution_state” field inside the “outputFields” in a custom code inside a workflow.

This is what I am passing in the callback:
```callback({
    outputFields: {
      hs_execution_state: "BLOCK"
    }
  });```
In the output I have a duplicated “hs_execution_state”, as you can see in the attached screenshot…

The custom code status appears as “Success”, so It goes to the next action, but It should block everything

<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/automation/custom-workflow-actions#execution|Here> you can find the documentation regarding this.
